basic.c:10:3: use_g_strlcpy: Use g_strlcpy(dst, src, sizeof(dst)) instead of strcpy — no bounds checking
basic.c:13:3: use_g_strlcpy: Use g_strlcat(dst, src, sizeof(dst)) instead of strcat — no bounds checking
basic.c:16:3: use_g_strlcpy: Use g_strlcat(dst, src, sizeof(dst)) instead of strncat — strncat's n parameter is the max to append, not the buffer size, which is error-prone
